# Project Architecture

This is a React 18 application using JavaScript (JSX), Vite, Tailwind CSS, and Zod.

## Structure

- src/features/<name>/ - Self-contained feature modules with layers: models, validators, utils, services, hooks, components, pages, index.js
- src/pages/ - App-level pages only (Home, NotFound). Feature pages live inside their feature.
- src/shared/ - Shared UI components, API client, error handling, theme tokens, constants, formatters
- src/routes/ - Centralized routing with guards, lazy loading, and route constants
- src/context/ - React context providers (AuthContext)
- src/config/ - Application configuration

## Rules

1. Features are self-contained. Never import from one feature into another.
2. Components never call APIs directly. Use: service -> hook -> component.
3. Pages are thin wrappers. They wire routing to hooks and pass data to layouts.
4. All data shapes use Zod schemas in the models layer.
5. Validation goes through validator functions, not inline.
6. Import from feature barrel exports, not internal paths.
7. No TypeScript. JavaScript with JSX only.
8. Shared code lives in src/shared/, never duplicated in features.
9. Do not generate documentation files unless explicitly requested.
